W: Yes. And I put the teddy bear on the 
bookshelves.
M: Oh, that’s cute! Why didn’t you put the 
tree in the corner next to the 
bookshelves? There’s some extra space. 
W: I thought I the tree would block the clock. So  placed it next to the table.
M: I guess you’re right. Oh, you put the 
bulletin board on the left side of the 
room.
W: Yes, I wanted it to be beside the clock 
so that more people look at it.
M: That’s a great idea! The children will 
see it whenever they check the time.
